  "title": "A Drone Hit a JetBlue Plane at 3,000 Feet Over NYC",
  "script": "A drone hit a plane? A JetBlue flight from Las Vegas was on final approach to JFK International Airport Monday morning when the pilot reported a collision — a drone, striking the jet right above the cockpit at 3,000 feet. Flight 948 landed safely. Passengers deplaned normally. A post-flight inspection found zero damage. But here's the kicker: the same morning, a nearby helicopter reported almost hitting a model airplane — a completely separate incident in the same airspace. The FAA is now investigating both. Nobody got hurt. No windows blown out, no emergency landing, no chaos. Just a commercial jet and a small drone sharing the sky at 3,000 feet over New York — which, apparently, is just a Monday morning now. So whose drone was it?",
